  "response_text": "Here's a grocery list for a family of four for one week, covering breakfast, lunch, dinner, and snacks. Feel free to adjust based on dietary preferences and restrictions!\n\n### Grocery List\n\n#### Produce\n- 1 bag of spinach or mixed greens\n- 1 head of broccoli\n- 1 bell pepper (any color)\n- 1 zucchini\n- 4 medium carrots\n- 1 cucumber\n- 1 pint of cherry tomatoes\n- 4 bananas\n- 4 apples\n- 1 bag of grapes\n- 1 lemon\n- 1 avocado\n- 1 bunch of bananas\n- 1 small bunch of fresh herbs (e.g., cilantro or parsley)\n\n#### Protein\n- 2 lbs of chicken breasts or thighs\n- 1 lb ground beef or turkey\n- 1 dozen eggs\n- 1 can of chickpeas or black beans\n- 1 lb of fish (e.g., salmon or tilapia)\n- 1 package of tofu (optional for vegetarian meals)\n\n#### Dairy\n- 1 gallon of milk (or plant-based alternative)\n- 1 lb of cheese (cheddar, mozzarella, or your preference)\n- 1 container of yogurt (plain or flavored)\n- 1 tub of cream cheese (optional)\n\n#### Grains\n- 1 loaf of whole grain bread\n- 1 package of tortillas (flour or corn)\n- 1 box of cereal or oatmeal\n- 1 bag of rice (brown or white)\n- 1 box of pasta\n\n#### Pantry Items\n- Olive oil or vegetable oil\n- Balsamic vinegar\n- Peanut butter or almond butter\n- Honey or maple syrup\n- Canned tomatoes (diced or crushed)\n- Spices (salt, pepper, garlic powder, Italian seasoning)\n- Stock or broth (chicken or vegetable)\n- 1 package of nuts (e.g., almonds or walnuts)\n\n#### Snacks\n- Granola bars\n- Popcorn\n- Hummus\n- Baby carrots or celery sticks\n- 1 bag of tortilla chips (for dipping)\n\n### Meal Ideas\n- **Breakfast**: Scrambled eggs with spinach and toast, yogurt with fruit, cereal with milk.\n- **Lunch**: Chicken salad wraps, hummus with veggies, and sandwiches with cheese and veggies.\n- **Dinner**: \n   - Grilled chicken with broccoli and rice\n   - Tacos with ground beef, cheese, and veggies\n   - Baked fish with zucchini and quinoa\n   - Stir-fried tofu with mixed vegetables and rice\n   - Pasta with tomato sauce and a side salad\n- **Snacks**: Fruits, nuts, granola bars, yogurt, and popcorn.\n\nThis list provides a good balance of nutrients and variety for the week. Adjust quantities based on your family's specific needs!",
